=== CONTEXT: Splash screen + Ollama first-launch fix ===

PROBLEM:
On first launch (Linux/Windows), Ollama is not yet downloaded.
Two issues were found:

1. SPLASH BLOCKS SETUP SCREEN
   - The splash (#splash div in index.html) covers the entire viewport at z-index 9999
   - It was previously removed in AppLayout's useEffect
   - But on first launch, ollamaReady === false → App renders OllamaSetupScreen, NOT AppLayout
   - AppLayout never mounts → splash never removed → user can't click the download button

   FIX: Splash removal moved to App.tsx, triggered by useEffect watching ollamaReady.
   When ollamaReady resolves to ANY value (true or false), the splash is removed.
   This covers both paths: setup screen (false) and normal app (true → AppLayout).

2. SIDECAR LAUNCHED WITHOUT BINARY
   - lib.rs setup() called start_sidecar() unconditionally
   - On first launch, ollama binary doesn't exist yet → start_sidecar errors
   - Not a crash (error is caught), but unnecessary noise + orphan kill attempt

   FIX: start_sidecar() now gated behind ollama_binary_path().is_ok()

FILES CHANGED:
- src/App.tsx — splash removal useEffect added, watches ollamaReady
- src/components/layout/app-layout.tsx — splash useEffect removed (was here before)
- src-tauri/src/lib.rs — sidecar start gated behind binary existence

IF PROBLEM PERSISTS ON LINUX:
- Check that #splash div exists in the DOM (inspect element)
- Check that ollamaReady state transitions happen (console.log in the useEffect)
- The 150ms setTimeout + rAF might need adjustment if Linux renders slower
- Verify is_ollama_installed IPC command returns false correctly on Linux
